      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): preserve claude-cli last-call usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- keep Claude CLI stream-json `result` usage as aggregate run usage\n- track latest assistant-message usage separately as `lastCallUsage`\n- use `lastCallUsage` for CLI session context snapshots so summed `result.cache_read_input_tokens` cannot inflate fresh token accounting\n\nFixes #85573\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBefore this patch, a Claude stream-json turn with two assistant usage records and a final result usage sum exposed only the final aggregate result usage to the CLI runner. That made `agentMeta.lastCallUsage` equal the summed `result.cache_read_input_tokens` value:\n\n```text\nassistant[0].cache_read_input_tokens = 18499\nassistant[1].cache_read_input_tokens = 27142\nresult.cache_read_input_tokens = 45641\nold lastCallUsage.cacheRead = 45641\n```\n\nAfter this patch, the parser keeps aggregate `usage` unchanged for run accounting but also exposes the latest assistant-call usage as `lastCallUsage`, and the CLI runner prefers that for session context snapshots:\n\n```text\nusage.cacheRead = 45641\nlastCallUsage.cacheRead = 27142\n```\n\nThis is covered by the new focused regression in `src/agents/cli-output.test.ts`: `uses latest Claude assistant usage as lastCallUsage when result usage is aggregate`. The regression constructs the summed Claude stream-json fixture directly and asserts both values separately.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/cli-output.test.ts` -> PASS, 16 tests\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/command/session-store.test.ts` -> PASS, 54 tests\n- `NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=16384 npx tsc --noEmit` -> PASS\n\n## Notes\n- First `tsc --noEmit` attempt with 8 GB heap OOMed before diagnostics; reran with 16 GB heap and passed.\n- `prettier --check` flags pre-existing wrapping in `src/agents/cli-runner.ts` if run on the whole file; I kept the cli-runner diff minimal instead of reformatting unrelated lines.\n",
